Sentencas: This paper reported on the fabrication of tri-layered oxygen transport membranes, porous vertical bar dense vertical bar porous Zr0.84Y0.16O2-delta-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-delta (YSZ-LSCF), by the tape casting, tape lamination and co-firing techniques.
Titulo: Influence of Impregnated Nano-scale LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ Particles on the Oxygen Permeation Performance of Zr0.84Y0.16O2-δ-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ Composite Membranes

Sentencas: Catalytically active nano-scale particles of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-delta (LNF) were impregnated into the porous scaffolds.
Titulo: Influence of Impregnated Nano-scale LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ Particles on the Oxygen Permeation Performance of Zr0.84Y0.16O2-δ-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ Composite Membranes

Sentencas: In order to quantatively determine the resistances of the oxygen reduction or evolution reactions against oxygen permeation, an additional dense YSZ layer was introduced inside the dense YSZ-LSCF permeation layer.
Titulo: Influence of Impregnated Nano-scale LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ Particles on the Oxygen Permeation Performance of Zr0.84Y0.16O2-δ-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ Composite Membranes

Sentencas: Electro-chemical measurements on the resulting five-layered solid oxide fuel cells showed a large reduction in the interfacial polarization resistances at the presence of these LNF catalysts, with the lowest values observed at the LNF loadings of 12wt%.
Titulo: Influence of Impregnated Nano-scale LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ Particles on the Oxygen Permeation Performance of Zr0.84Y0.16O2-δ-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ Composite Membranes

Sentencas: In particular, the cathodic and anodic polarization resistances were 0.26 and 0.08 Omega.cm(2) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Influence of Impregnated Nano-scale LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ Particles on the Oxygen Permeation Performance of Zr0.84Y0.16O2-δ-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ Composite Membranes

Sentencas: The oxygen permeation flux under the air/CH4 gradient was 7.6 mL/(cm.min), which was 14 times higher than the measured value for the blank YSZ-LSCF membrane.
Titulo: Influence of Impregnated Nano-scale LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ Particles on the Oxygen Permeation Performance of Zr0.84Y0.16O2-δ-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ Composite Membranes

Sentencas: Further impedance analysis indicated that the charge transfer step during oxygen reduction may limit the overall oxygen permeation process.
Titulo: Influence of Impregnated Nano-scale LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ Particles on the Oxygen Permeation Performance of Zr0.84Y0.16O2-δ-La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ Composite Membranes
